<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Hind2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Hind,</orth> 1) a menial, servant: <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.5.99" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 5, 99</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.1.20" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 1, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.1.73" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 1, 73</bibl>.<lb />2) a boor, a peasant, any mean person: <bibl n="shak. err 3.1.77" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 1, 77</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 1.2.123" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 2, 123</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.3.16" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 3, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.271" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 271</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.2.130" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 130</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.4.33" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 33</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.3.77" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 3, 77</bibl>.
